author: maxb
msg: SWIG: Macro mania!  Use macros to simplify the many many repetitive declarations
of callback typemaps.
* include/svn_types.swg (%callback_typemap, %callback_typemap_maybenull):
Define new macros.
* svn_delta.i, svn_fs.i, svn_ra.i, svn_repos.i, svn_wc.i:
Simplify a lot using the new macros.
* svn_client.i: Simplify a lot using the new macros.
(%authprompt_callback_typemap): Define new macro, and use it to simplify
further.

author: maxb
msg: SWIG: Miscellaneous tidying.
[in subversion/bindings/swig/]
* svn_fs.i, svn_repos.i: Remove overly-obvious or incorrect comments.
Wrap long lines. Add FIXMEs. Group Ruby pool convention workarounds in
contiguous sections.

author: maxb
msg: * subversion/bindings/swig/svn_ra.i: Oops, group like things together,
not unlike things together!

author: maxb
msg: SWIG/Perl: Generalize the svn_delta_editor_t typemap in svn_delta.i to the
same name as the Ruby one, so the existing %apply statement works for Perl
too, and therefore delete the duplicate typemaps in other files.
Net effect: the editor args of svn_wc_transmit_text_deltas2(),
svn_wc_transmit_text_deltas(), and svn_wc_transmit_prop_deltas() get
wrapped for Perl.
[in subversion/bindings/swig/]
* svn_delta.i: Switch name of typemap to general one.
* svn_ra.i, svn_repos.i: Delete redundant typemaps.
